raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  ten (10) years Functional Responsibility:  Under broad direction leads client programs and plays a major role in developing recommendations.  Proficiently applies consulting methodologies to collect and analyze data.  Leads the development of programs and the implementation of solutions to meet the client’s business needs.  Applies extensive knowledge of client’s industry and information technology to meet the objectives of the engagement.  Coordinates planning the engagement, establishing the engagement requirements, managing the profitability of the engagement, and delivering the results to the client.  Develops and assists in making client presentations. Minimum Education:  Master’s degree in engineering, management, information systems or a related field with a minimum of ten (10) years general experience of which five (5) years must be specialized; or a Bachelor’s degree in engineering, computer science, information systems or a related field or fifteen (15) years must be specialized.

raw_data.title: Analyst I
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:   Possesses five (5) years of experience in systems requirements.  Supports the development of system and programming specifications.  Aids with data processing solutions based on business need and technical considerations.  Researches and assists with resolution of problems.  Assists with complex documentation and user needs analysis.  Studies customer environment by analyzing job tasks, organizational structure, and user requirements to propose system-wide solutions.  Interviews technical personnel, interprets reports, specifications, and drawings to increase understanding of processes and requirements. Functional Responsibility:  Under close supervision, provides research and analysis support.  Researches and analyzes data related to a project topic.  Applies industry knowledge to determine the accuracy and reasonableness of the data.  Documents and summarizes the results to be used in developing client recommendations.  Assists in developing programs and implementing solutions to meet the client’s business needs.  Utilizes knowledge of information technology and the client’s industry to support members of the team.   Minimum Education:  Bachelor’s degree in information systems or a related field and ten (10) years general experience of which five (5) years must be specialized; or ten (10) years related experience.

raw_data.title: Full Stack Developer
raw_data.description: General Experience/Qualifications:  Ten (10) years’ experience.  Skills/Qualifications at a minimum:  - Proficiency with C#, C++, OO, .net 2.1-4.5, SQL Server - Proficiency with Web applications, windows applications, web services, and windows services - Knowledge of and ability to follow IA and system development standards - Self-starter with ability to work alone or as part of a team    - Excellent communication and interpersonal skills - Ability to obtain a security clearance  Specialized Experience:  Eight (8) years of full stack development experience for all aspects of system development.  Functional Responsibility:  Responsible for all aspects of system development, to include requirements definition, system design, architecture, development/coding, testing, deployment, sustainment, etc.  Develop system requirements by conferring with users’/process owners and accommodating systems flow, data usage, and work processes.  Create systems by using variety of languages and design tools.  Improve system performance by consulting with clients and applying appropriate problems solving skills to root-cause problems and develop effective solutions.  Monitor system performance to ensure critical processes are functioning and stable.  Report project status to company leaders and clients.  Minimum Education/Experience:  Master's Degree with 8 years or Bachelor’s Degree with 10 years

raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience: Possesses knowledge in computer programming, software design and integration, and participation with software design teams. raw_data.title: Network Administrator
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  five (5) years Functional Responsibility:  The Network Administrator is a member on the technical staff. This individual must have experience in the design and development of Client-Server and Web Enabled Corporate applications including LAN/WAN network topology. Must be able to Install and troubleshoot network infrastructure problems and administer network management tools. This individual can conduct an engineering assessment and impact analysis for adding new hardware or software to an existing network environment. Minimum Education:  Must have a minimum of five years (5) experience in managing networks and Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field or 8 year relevant experience.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert (SME)
raw_data.description: Functional Responsibility:  Leads, facilitates and organizes solution development for program involving extensive scope and complexity.  Has extensive Technical and Functional understanding facilitating the interpreting, organizing, executing, and coordinating IT engagements relative to a particular domain through successful delivery. Makes integrated Functional and technical decisions, which are considered authoritative, and which demonstrate mature judgment in anticipating and solving complex problems. Work requires the technical capability to assess the cost, schedule performance implications of existing and projected technological advances, as well as being able to evaluate the impact of new and innovative technology solution strategies.    Minimum Education:  Minimum requirement is a Master’s degree in the relevant Technical or Functional field, 12 years of management and strategy consulting experience. Five (5) years of business and technology leadership.
